==Development==
''Skateboardin{{'}}'' was one of the first games announced from Absolute Entertainment.{{sfn|Computer Entertainer|1987|p=9|ref=AtoAE}}

==Legacy==
A follow-up titled ''Super Skateboardin''' was released in December 1988 for the [[Atari 7800]].{{sfn|Computer Entertainer includes the Video Game Update|1989|p=14|ref=AU}}

''Skate Boardin''' was re-released in 2002, as part of the [[Activision Anthology]] collection.{{fact|date=June 2024}}

